Direct Known Subclasses:
ConditionallyMergeOverlappingObjects, NonMaximaSuppression
public abstract class ReduceElementsGreedy<T>
extends ReduceElements<T>
Reduces the number or spatial-extent of elements by favouring higher-confidence elements over lower-confidence elements.

Elements can be removed entirely, or can have other operations executed (e.g. removing overlapping voxels).

  1. Select highest-confidence proposal, remove from list, add to output.
  2. Compare this proposal with remaining proposals, and process any overlapping elements (removing or otherwise altering).
  3. If there are remaining proposals in the queue, goto Step 1.
Author:
Owen Feehan

      public List<WithConfidence<T>> reduce​(List<WithConfidence<T>> elements)
      Description copied from class: ReduceElements
      Reduce a list of elements (each with a confidence score) to a smaller-list.

      See the class javadoc for details of algorithm.

      It is not guaranteed that the resulting list will have fewer elements than the input list, but never more.

    • possibleOverlappingObjects

      protected abstract java.util.function.Predicate<T> possibleOverlappingObjects​(T source, Iterable<WithConfidence<T>> others)
      Finds a subset of others that possibly overlap with the source element.

      This is not a definite list of element, but must contain all possible overlapping element, and should be efficient.

      This is the first filtering step. The resulting list will then be further filtered by includePossiblyOverlappingObject(T, T).

      Parameters:
      source - the element we are currently processing, for which we search for possibly overlapping element
      others - other element that could possibly overlap with source but need to be filtered.

    • includePossiblyOverlappingObject

      protected abstract boolean includePossiblyOverlappingObject​(T source, T other)
      Whether to include another (possibly-overlapping with source) element in processing?

      This is the second filtering step (after possibleOverlappingObjects(Object, Iterable).

      Parameters:
      source - the element we are currently processing, for which we search for possibly overlapping element
      other - another object which we are considering to include in processing (in conjunction with source).
      Returns:
      true iff other should be included in processing.

    • processOverlapping

      protected abstract boolean processOverlapping​(WithConfidence<T> source, WithConfidence<T> overlapping, Runnable removeOverlapping, java.util.function.Consumer<T> changeSource)
      Processes an object that is deemed to overlap
      Parameters:
      source - the element that is being processed as the source, the object with higher confidence.
      overlapping - the element that is deemed to overlap with the sourceElement about which a decision is to be made.
      removeOverlapping - a runnable that can be called to remove overlappingElement, if this decision is taken.
      changeSource - a runnable that can ne called to change the source-element, if this decision is taken.
      Returns:
      true if the source object was altered during processing, false if it was not.
